Done !

00:28:30.330 --> 00:28:35.629
&gt;&gt; Female #4: I loved when you sang "For Good"
for Oprah for her last show as her Morehead

00:28:35.629 --> 00:28:36.809
graduates surrounded her.

00:28:36.809 --> 00:28:37.809
&gt;&gt; Kristen: Thank you

00:28:37.809 --> 00:28:42.769
&gt;&gt; Female #4: And I was wondering what did
you envision a moment like that for yourself,

00:28:42.769 --> 00:28:43.769
what would that moment be?

00:28:43.769 --> 00:28:45.139
Who has changed you for the better?

00:28:45.139 --> 00:28:46.779
&gt;&gt; Kristin: Oh my God, I love this question.

00:28:46.779 --> 00:28:48.549
Nobody has ever asked me that.

00:28:48.549 --> 00:28:50.029
&gt;&gt; Female #4: Are you serious?

00:28:50.029 --> 00:28:54.179
I actually though; "She's probably been asked
this over and over again."

00:28:54.179 --> 00:28:58.889
&gt;&gt; Kristin: I would never be, could never
be famous enough or good enough to be Oprah,

00:28:58.889 --> 00:29:01.139
but that moment, um.

00:29:01.139 --> 00:29:11.679
Oh, man, I love this question, I think obviously
we all look for ways to give back and I do

00:29:11.679 --> 00:29:20.969
have a charity [ laughs ] Cause I know people
are going "of course" But I do, I love animals

00:29:20.969 --> 00:29:22.919
and I have a charity called Maddie's Corner.

00:29:22.919 --> 00:29:27.369
My dog Madeline Kahn, she started the charity.

00:29:27.369 --> 00:29:31.109
She whispered through her paw one night; "start
this charity under my name."

00:29:31.109 --> 00:29:36.940
But it basically helps animals get placed
into the right home for them.

00:29:36.940 --> 00:29:43.649
Because a lot of times we hear about dog that
get, you know, into a very kid friendly and

00:29:43.649 --> 00:29:44.870
they are not used to kids.

00:29:44.870 --> 00:29:50.249
So it helps facilitate that and sometimes
people who need animals, so it's animals helping

00:29:50.249 --> 00:29:53.009
people helping animals is the theme.

00:29:53.009 --> 00:29:59.149
So, in my perfect world, and we are a long
way from this, is that every displaced dog

00:29:59.149 --> 00:30:04.470
or cat or bird or snake or whatever, would
be in the right home.

00:30:04.470 --> 00:30:10.450
Like, I could image if someone was singing
"For Good" and I was an old lady and like

00:30:10.450 --> 00:30:16.889
all these dogs and cats and you know, with
their owners, I would just die.

00:30:16.889 --> 00:30:20.379
I just love animals, I just love them.

00:30:20.379 --> 00:30:23.190
And I love children too, those who can't speak
for themselves.

00:30:23.190 --> 00:30:28.970
Just, it kills me, I cannot, if I see a St.
Jude commercial, I am like [ crying ] here

00:30:28.970 --> 00:30:30.249
is $70,000.

00:30:30.249 --> 00:30:32.949
I won't be able to eat but I don't care.

00:30:32.949 --> 00:30:36.960
[ laughter ] I just can't if someone's been
abused or hurt or can't help themselves, I

00:30:36.960 --> 00:30:42.159
just can't, I know everybody is the same,
it's not like I am special in this belief,

00:30:42.159 --> 00:30:44.359
but that would be my moment.

00:30:44.359 --> 00:30:47.649
Thank you for asking me that, that was an
incredible moment for her to see what she

00:30:47.649 --> 00:30:48.649
has done.

00:30:48.649 --> 00:30:51.249
&gt;&gt; Female #5: [Inaudible]

00:30:51.249 --> 00:30:55.889
